Mod.Description:
Enchances pawns' perception of nature.

   Simple mod that adjusts beauty and ugly modifiers for terrain and flora. Most notable changes:
      
         - flowers are significantly more beautiful now;
            - most trees have beauty increased to 2-4 range. Oak and Teak trees have 5 beauty;
               - grass and most bush plants have 1 beauty. Berry plants and healroot have 2 beauty;
                  - water has overall beauty increased to 4 with ocean cost line having beauty of 6;
                     - soil, sand and ice get neutral beauty, rich soil gets 1 beauty;
                        - mud and marsh are really dislikable for the pawns now (-4 and -6 beauty);
                           - rafflesia is adjusted to -12 beauty to correspond its description;
                              - chunks and stone blocks are more tolerable with -4 and -6 beauty (against -8 and -12 in Vanilla. Ouch!).

Allows your colonists to do things smarter. Check mod settings for more information.
- chinese simplified by chrisxlite, HawnHan;
   - chinese traditional by Lak4CYUT;
      - german by Katinka1988;
         - french by qux;
            - spanish by Crusader;

Vanilla Apparel Expanded is part of a series of mods expanding on everyday life on the Rimworld. When paired together with a brand new Vanilla Weapons Expanded and Vanilla Armours Expanded, you can bring something to your game that will keep you interested in it for days.

   Apparel is distributed into several new technologies that need to be researched, expanding the life of the game and possibly leading to some interesting choices - research a way to get off this planet? Or maybe learn how to craft jeans and workwear?
      
         This mod adds a wide selection of apparel with useful effects, including but not limited to:
            Gas masks protecting from toxicity;
               Jumpsuits and aprons for work speed boost;
                  Doctor scrubs and Chef’s uniforms.
